[![](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2019/01/50464602_10161268950800640_2803280924525985792_o-800x450.jpg)](https://www.facebook.com/groundviews/photos/a.10161268942885640/10161268950795640/?type=3&theater)

斯里蘭卡採茶工人日前舉行團結示威，要求將基本日薪提高到1000斯里蘭卡盧比。圖片來自全球之聲夥伴網站Groundviews。

2019年1月23日，Thousand
Movement這個由各工會以及草根運動者集合而成的社團同時在斯里蘭卡的[30個地點](https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2018/12/06/plan-d06.html)[舉辦示威活動](https://viacampesina.org/en/thousand-
movement-srilankan-tea-plantation-workers-to-protest-in-30-locations-for-
better-daily-
wages/)，呼籲茶業公司將斯里蘭卡採茶工人的最低日薪資增加到[1000斯里蘭卡盧比(約5.5美金)](http://www.dailymirror.lk/article/-movement-
protests-in-
Colombo-161465.html)，或是將目前的最低日薪增加一倍。示威者表示，由於生活支出日益增加，但是薪資成長停滯不前，導致有越來越多的採茶工人落入貧困當中。根據「土地農業改革運動」(Movement
for Land and Agricultural Reform，MONLAR)主席 [Chinthaka
Rajapakshe](https://viacampesina.org/en/thousand-movement-srilankan-tea-
plantation-workers-to-protest-in-30-locations-for-better-daily-wages/)表示：

> 日前佩拉德尼亞大學(University of
> Peradeniya)的研究者發現，在茶葉產區，一個人要有27,707盧比(約152美金)一個月的收入才能維持基本生活所需。但是平均而言，採茶工人的月薪不到8000盧比(約44美金)。

> Generations of
> [#plantationworkers](https://twitter.com/hashtag/plantationworkers?src=hash&ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw)
> have propped up our economy by toiling under deplorable conditions from
> 6am-6pm, come rain or shine. Don’t the producers of the “Pure Ceylon Tea” we
> proudly boast of deserve a decent day’s wage at the very least?
